<br>
Also, I was wondering if bolt spells would be a problem with a gnome's height.  I have a halfling and human ranger and it seems the arrows come out of the halfling's head and the human's waist.  Are the bolt spells similiar to that?<br>
<br>
Thanks for your help! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iblisthemage>IblisTheMage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 2:35:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8004.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.decara.com/eq/Federico6060.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Starting a gnome magician, few questions</span><hr size=1> Be a DE, they are much more pretty than gnomes =).<br>
<br>
Bolts are good for pulling, but for conjuration mages the &quot;shock&quot; line DD is pretty much the way to go. A single blocked bolt reduces the efficiency of bolts overall tremendously... <p>Iblis<br>
Archmage of the Heralds of Dawn<br>
Karana</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shanukdandiprat>ShanukDandiprat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 3:08:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8004.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Starting a gnome magician, few questions</span><hr size=1> You have chosen wisely.  Gnome mages &gt; all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Religion is not really important for you.  Being an agnostic gnome means that you will not be KoS in most places, which is nice.  Still, there is nothing wrong with choosing a religion if you want to, there is just no real advantage to doing so.<br>
<br>
Height does not really matter with bolts.  The bolt actually gets fired from the midpoint of the target regardless of how tall the caster is (it will hit much higher on a hill giant than on a snake--hard to tell without the graphics working but that's how it is).  Shooting from elevation can be helpful, but being a gnome rather than an elf or a human isn't going to matter.<br>
<br>
Shanuk Dandiprat<br>
Conjurer of Drinal<br>
