<br>
If I was making another character, I'd try to make one that wasn't agnostic.  You never know when they will add more diety specific items and many of them turn out to be fairly nice.  Diety specific items, while fairly nice, aren't usually that amazing so being agnostic because you want to be able to use more cities isn't a bad thing.  In the end, I think it comes down to how you want to play your character.  My mage is agnostic, but I play her as if she worships the father of her race. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108671">Varia Darselai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pag0>Pag0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 5:09:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8004.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fallenalliance.org/screenshots/downwpst.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Starting a gnome magician, few questions</span><hr size=1> Anyone who tries to talk you out of being Gnome is simply jealous.<br>
